{"id": "EUVD-2025-12890", "enisaUuid": "64317aea-b4dd-3276-9788-2c0ef7c83b72", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nbpftool: Fix NULL pointer dereference when pin {PROG, MAP, LINK} without FILE\n\nWhen using bpftool to pin {PROG, MAP, LINK} without FILE,\nsegmentation fault will occur. The reson is that the lack\nof FILE will cause strlen to trigger NULL pointer dereference.\nThe corresponding stacktrace is shown below:\n\ndo_pin\n  do_pin_any\n    do_pin_fd\n      mount_bpffs_for_pin\n        strlen(name) <- NULL pointer dereference\n\nFix it by adding validation to the common process.", "datePublished": "2025-05-01T14:10:24", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T16:03:25", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-49875", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/34de8e6e0e1f66e431abf4123934a2581cb5f133", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6dcdd1b68b7f9333d48d48fc77b75e7f235f6a4a", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8c80b2fca4112d724dde477aed13f7b0510a2792", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/da5161ba94c5e9182c301dd4f09c94f715c068bd"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49875", "GHSA-c8r4-j2q4-mjgj"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "25a1298f-513a-3e84-ae25-82adca0d2fda", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "54c896d0-24f3-3e3e-989a-fb110a47ccdf", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "75a1e792c335b5c6d7fdb1014da47aeb64c5944f <6dcdd1b68b7f9333d48d48fc77b75e7f235f6a4a"}, {"id": "55c8188a-3867-3f3f-8ae1-280762bd7b3d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.7"}, {"id": "85213c1a-d1ca-3afd-836b-0398817796b0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "75a1e792c335b5c6d7fdb1014da47aeb64c5944f <34de8e6e0e1f66e431abf4123934a2581cb5f133"}, {"id": "89b09595-1087-35c1-870b-5096ee8b9707", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.